review_blob: Nice aroma with citrusy orange tagged to it. Nice foamy head with a nice aroma and tasty finish. Would drink again.
Great double IPA that I think needs more attention. Definitely one of the best on the market. Price for 22oz is very reasonable as well.
On tap. Pours an amber color with nice foamy head. Distinct floral hops with a nice citrus bitter finish
Pour clear with nice fluffy head to it. Aroma is enticing and the taste is even more impressive. Very good belgian sourness to it. Easy one of Stones best.
Pour clear, taste is sour, with a hint of peaches. Definitely needs more peach flavor but overall not a bad beer.
Caramel head with a nice florally taste. The color is pleasant with a nice finish.
Very interesting beer. The floral and citrus combined makes for a very interesting and tasty beer from Boulevard.
Very floral but distinct and roasty. The malt of the beer comes out and begins to expand its aromoas upon pouring. Very solid beer.
Great aroma when first poured. The distinct taste of good hops comes out and begins to make your palate salivate. Taste is smooth with a nice bitter finish. Love this beer!
